    {
      "id": "d369b37038b8bb37c131ddd54601bb546079ee9b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 263,
        "name": "Henri Doreau",
        "email": "henri.doreau@cea.fr",
        "username": "hdoreau"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-05 10:43:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks Di for working on this. Your patch obviously covers more than the unlink case my patch aimed to fix, which is good.\n\nIt seems to me that this introduces several redundant checks of is_obf and is_dot_lustre though.\n\nFor the sake of layering cleanness, I'd suggest to move the (necessary) checks from the MDT to the MDD layer, and let the obf and dot_lustre md_dir_operations handle things. \n\nUnless I'm missing something that should allow the checks to be performed only when needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c7b9d72604b81044a9bbd7df38d600fd91a39958",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-05 10:56:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "12d4f673481329713528b7c87940852f76b8d969",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-03-05 13:17:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/71bc585a-8592-11e2-9f8d-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0897b7f2e2bce9bea9d2beda2abdb7a47a43e86a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-05 17:37:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWhen it comes to DNE, we'd better catch OBF or .lustre earlier(on MDT layer), otherwise, it will try to do getattr of these two remote objects(OBF and .lustre) before it comes to MDD.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "28569b5f81a4d408792db5134007889dc12b88b3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 19:15:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nMy comment on permission changes notwithstanding, this patch is ready to land.  Since http://review.whamcloud.com/5298 needs to be refreshed anyway, this patch could land and remove both checks at that time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4ececbc12ed5c5d8eac18396e2b4d2e85c84f283",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 19:39:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2d53fca7f43eca0753fe2e7e7c7962b4da76be82",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 19:52:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: (1 inline comment)\n\nActually, I take back my previous comment - there doesn't seem to be any value to changing access to .lustre itself.  The access control can be managed for individual files below .lustre as needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
